          university-level competition that challenges students to design,
          build, and test a rover capable of operating in Mars-like conditions.
          Hosted by the Canadian Space Technology Advancement Group (CSTAG), the
          competition fosters innovation in space robotics while providing
          students with hands-on experience in mechanical design, electronics,
          and software development. Throughout the challenge, teams must
          simulate real-world space exploration scenarios, tackling complex
          tasks such as autonomous navigation, object manipulation, and terrain
          traversal. Sidus Robotics is excited to take on this challenge,
          representing Memorial University and contributing to the future of
          space technology.
        </p>

